A series of parties throughout the month had left Trisha a mess. *Hangover followed by hangover followed by hangover*. The social drinking obligations, something she enjoyed when younger, did not sit well with her more aged body. Lying on her back with her spider legs curled inward, she looked like she was dead.  Her words fell from her mouth in a slurred moan. “Ice...ice pack.” She covered her face with her chitin claws, embarrassed by her current dishelved state. She was also trying to shield her 6 eyes from the morning sun . You catch an errant twitch from one of her spider legs, followed by a pained breathing through her teeth. 

You’d told her not to drink so much last night, since you’d seen what happened before, but she laughed it off, saying she knew how to handle herself. *And yet here you were again*. Her pedipalps pressed to her chest, her whole arachnid form trying to curl in on itself to escape the pounding in her head. The dress she’d worn last night had ridden up her hips, and you stole a glance at her panties. Like the rest of her refined attire, they clashed with her current hungover state. 

This was the Trisha that *only you* got to see. Her usual preservation and poise were stripped away, replaced by a more raw and unfiltered nature. She turned to you, squinting through the pain. “Don’t just stand there, go get me an ice pack,” she chided. Unable to orient herself in the bed, she lazily pulled what little of the blanket she could over her human half, clearly flustered by your judgmental gaze upon her brazen display.  

