cards.first_message:
The forest is quiet. The solitude speaks to you as branches sway and a soft breeze cuts through them, whistling as it goes. An abandoned firewatch tower stands alone in a clearing just ahead of you. Despite its age, it looks to be in decent condition. Cobwebs and vines wrap around the bottom support beams, as if the forest itself were trying to subsume it. A mountain range saws into the horizon north of the clearing. The forest forms a cavelike darkness behind you. The sun is creeping behind the wall of foliage to your left. It was time to set up camp for the night before the darkness swallowed you up.

After scaling the metal stairway to the cabin atop the superstructure, you find the firewatch tower is in better shape than you anticipated. Signs of intermittent use sprinkle the dilapidated space. Empty beer cans, an ash pile in the old wood-burning stove tucked against the wall, miscellaneous refuse scattered about the floor, and some graffiti carved into the walls and floors from prior woodland explorers. By no means a five-star resort, but a comfy place to call home. 

The windows along the walls were mostly intact. One of them had shattered, and a patchwork of boards and duct tape covered the offending hole. The other windows were caked in grime, but you could see out of them well enough. The view was impeccable, and since you were at least 50 feet higher than you used to be, you'd gain another few minutes' worth of the setting sun before it slipped beneath the trees completely. 

You catch the glint of two eyes far into the dark forest canopy. The eyes stare back.  

<div class="sanity-meter" style="width:650px;text-align:center;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;margin:0 auto;">
    <div style="font-size:20px;color:#666;margin-bottom:5px;">~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~</div>
    <div style="width:100%;height:20px;background:#e0e0e0;border-radius:5px;overflow:hidden;margin:5px 0;">
        <div id="sanityFill" style="height:100%;background:#3b82f6;border-radius:5px;transition:width 0.5s ease,background-color 0.5s ease;width:100%;"></div>
    </div>
    <div style="font-size:20px;margin-top:5px;" id="sanityText">Sanity: 100%</div>
    <div style="font-size:24px;font-style:italic;margin-top:8px;color:#333;" id="sanityMsg">The forest is sublime.</div>
</div>

<script>
const sanityMessages = {
    100: "The forest is sublime.",
    80: "The forest whispers.",
    60: "It is calling out to you.",
    40: "You feel it beneath your skin.",
    20: "Your soul quivers.",
    0: "You are in danger."
};

function getSanityColor(level) {
    if (level >= 80) return '#3b82f6';
    if (level >= 60) return '#10b981';
    if (level >= 40) return '#f59e0b';
    if (level >= 20) return '#ef4444';
    return '#991b1b';
}

function getSanityMessage(level) {
    if (level >= 100) return sanityMessages[100];
    if (level >= 80) return sanityMessages[80];
    if (level >= 60) return sanityMessages[60];
    if (level >= 40) return sanityMessages[40];
    if (level >= 20) return sanityMessages[20];
    return sanityMessages[0];
}

function updateSanity(level) {
    level = Math.max(0, Math.min(100, level));
    const fill = document.getElementById('sanityFill');
    const text = document.getElementById('sanityText');
    const message = document.getElementById('sanityMsg');

    fill.style.width = level + '%';
    fill.style.backgroundColor = getSanityColor(level);
    text.textContent = 'Sanity: ' + level + '%';
    message.textContent = getSanityMessage(level);
